The military under the auspices of Operation Thunder Strike (OPTS) has informed the Kaduna State Government of the killing of a herder while grazing in Matyei village, Atyap Chiefdom of Zangon Kataf Local Government Area. According to the briefing, troops responded to a report of a farm destroyed in the village on Sunday afternoon, and arrived the scene to discover that a herder, one Ado Hassan, had been shot dead by unknown persons. Initial investigations into the killing led to the arrest of three persons identified as David Kure, Peter Adamu and Bulus Duniya. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Further investigations led to the arrest of two more persons namely Matthew Peter and  Yohanna Chawai  Monday morning. This was revealed In a statement signed by Samuel Aruwan,  Commissioner of internal Security and Home affairs, according to him, the arrested suspects are undergoing preliminary investigation. JUST IN: Saudi Arabia ‘To Open Airspace, Land, Sea Border’ With Qatar COVID-19: Kano Residents Plead For Enforcement Of Protocols In Public Places “Governor Nasir El-Rufai expressed dismay at the killing and sent condolences to the family of the herder, while praying for the repose of his soul. “He urged citizens to eschew jungle justice and embrace recourse to the law in the face of any incursion or offence, and further tasked security agencies to conduct thorough investigations into the killing. The statement said. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION